[Student "S"]
{NORTH would have responded 1\H if WEST had not overcalled. 
But with only 8 points he cannot bid at the 2-level. The Negative Double solves his problem, 
giving this information to partner.

SOUTH has good \Hs and enough points to bid game. 
Notice that if WEST had remained silent, NORTH would have responded 1\H, 
and SOUTH would have jumped to game.}

